of the Holmes brothers.

27:19.830 --> 27:21.434
MAN:
I knew it was a drug deal.

27:21.470 --> 27:23.802
That's why I stayed hidden,

27:23.840 --> 27:26.138
even after I heard the gunshots.

27:26.170 --> 27:28.070
I heard men screaming.

27:28.110 --> 27:31.807
I got up to run, and I saw him.

27:31.850 --> 27:34.273
He was sitting there
like a statue.

27:34.320 --> 27:36.276
His eyes, I...

27:36.320 --> 27:38.083
I don't know.

27:38.120 --> 27:40.315
They were just cold.

27:40.350 --> 27:42.318
Like the Arctic.

27:42.360 --> 27:44.851
The only man to ever
lay eyes on El Mecanico

27:44.890 --> 27:46.949
has a weakness for
unhelpful metaphors.

27:50.260 --> 27:52.160
Are you still sulking
about Mycroft?

27:52.200 --> 27:53.428
No.

27:53.470 --> 27:56.166
I hope you don't expect
me to apologize.

27:56.200 --> 27:58.202
Look, ifI had a sister,
would you even hesitate

27:58.240 --> 27:59.832
for a second before
you slept With her?

27:59.870 --> 28:01.770
It's not the act itself
that gives me pause.

28:01.810 --> 28:03.300
It's that I can't
put it into context.

28:04.880 --> 28:08.338
There is_a certain...
intimacy

28:08.380 --> 28:11.281
which is a byproduct
of our partnership.

28:11.320 --> 28:13.015
We work well
together,

28:13.050 --> 28:14.915
and I think we both
value that fact.

28:14.960 --> 28:16.313
Right?

28:16.360 --> 28:18.419
You must have known
that I would deduce

28:18.460 --> 28:20.325
that you had slept
with my brother.

28:22.160 --> 28:24.424
It is unlike you
to introduce such a free radical

28:24.470 --> 28:27.962
_ into an otherwise _
highly functional relationship.

28:28.000 --> 28:30.059
Unless, of course,
the unlikelihood

28:30.100 --> 28:32.967
was precisely
the point.

28:33.010 --> 28:35.308
Do you think you're maybe
overthinking this?

28:35.340 --> 28:37.376
You wanted to demonstrate
that I don't have

28:37.410 --> 28:39.344
a monopoly on boorish
or outrageous behavior.

28:39.380 --> 28:42.076
That you won't become
a slave to the roles

28:42.120 --> 28:44.042
we have assigned
each other.

28:44.090 --> 28:45.443
Hmm.

28:45.490 --> 28:48.118
I'm glad we cleared the air.

28:48.160 --> 28:49.912
Message received.

28:49.960 --> 28:51.427
There was no message.

28:51.460 --> 28:52.950
(sighs)

28:52.990 --> 28:54.924
Does that man's reliance
on hazy metaphor

28:54.960 --> 28:56.325
seem almost willful to you?

28:56.360 --> 28:58.328
What do you mean?

29:00.940 --> 29:03.238
I guess I thought
he looked like...

29:03.270 --> 29:06.307
Vengeance.

29:06.340 --> 29:08.308
MAN 2 (over video):
Vengeance. Okay.

29:08.340 --> 29:11.446
He's selling an idea,
not describing a person.

29:14.180 --> 29:17.479
I guess I thought
he looked like...

29:17.520 --> 29:19.408
Vengeance.

29:19.450 --> 29:21.156
Vengeance. Okay.

29:21.190 --> 29:23.385
Can you be
more specific?

29:27.360 --> 29:29.089
You're a crafty cow, aren't you?

29:29.130 --> 29:31.189
Look at his hand.

29:33.070 --> 29:35.197
He's missing his ring finger.

29:35.240 --> 29:38.334
As is the man who murdered
Dalton Ladd the other night.

29:38.370 --> 29:41.203
I don't think we're looking
at the witness to a massacre.

29:41.240 --> 29:43.970
I think he's the perpetrator.

29:45.280 --> 29:47.009
That's El Mecanico.

29:47.050 --> 29:49.848
GREGSON:
This is the guy
the Feds have been

29:49.880 --> 29:51.211
chasing for years?

29:51.250 --> 29:52.547
If that's true,
why did he even bother

29:52.590 --> 29:53.909
giving this statement?

29:53.960 --> 29:55.086
We think that
the police

29:55.120 --> 29:56.348
got to the scene
of the massacre

29:56.390 --> 29:57.516
before he could
get away.

29:57.560 --> 29:59.380
He had to come up
with a cover story.

29:59.430 --> 30:02.092
We're dealing with an
exceptionally cunning opponent.

30:02.130 --> 30:03.961
He'd have to have
this identity

30:04.000 --> 30:06.059
in place as
a fail-safe.

30:06.100 --> 30:08.239
Once the authorities
arrived, he crafted a tale

30:08.270 --> 30:10.363
that took advantage of
everyone's preconceived notions

30:10.400 --> 30:12.402
of what a cartel hit man
should look like.

30:12.440 --> 30:14.601
He sent the DEA
hunting for a myth.

30:14.640 --> 30:16.437
And no one noticed
that the guy's

30:16.480 --> 30:18.141
missing a finger
on his left hand?

30:18.180 --> 30:21.377
They've been working off
of partial fingerprints.

30:21.420 --> 30:23.411
No one knew that they were
pursuing a four-fingered man

30:23.450 --> 30:25.088
until we found _
a complete set of prints

30:25.120 --> 30:27.441
at the scene of
Dalton Ladd's murder.

30:27.490 --> 30:29.117
That's him.

30:29.160 --> 30:31.981
We're about to
apprehend El Mecanico.

30:32.030 --> 30:33.554
Well, let's say you're right.

30:33.590 --> 30:36.491
This guy told the Feds his name
was Kent Jenkins.

30:36.530 --> 30:37.929
I'm guessing that's an alias.

30:37.970 --> 30:39.392
All right, so we know

30:39.430 --> 30:41.432
what he looks like--
that's more than we had--

30:41.470 --> 30:44.928
but I don't see how we're
about to put cuffs on the guy.

30:44.970 --> 30:48.872
We know what he looks like,
and we know what he wants.

30:50.180 --> 30:52.501
El Mecanico is nothing
if not thorough.

30:52.550 --> 30:54.643
He was contracted to
kill Nigella Mason.

30:54.680 --> 30:57.240
Rest assured he's going to
try and do exactly that.

30:57.280 --> 30:59.544
We don't use civilians as bait.

30:59.590 --> 31:02.479
There's no need to put her
directly in his crosshairs.

31:02.520 --> 31:04.158
No.

31:04.190 --> 31:05.521
There's no doubt he's
monitoring her movements.

31:05.560 --> 31:07.425
One of the simplest ways
to do that

31:07.460 --> 31:08.996
is listen in on _
her phone conversations.

31:09.030 --> 31:11.169
Anyone with 50
pounds to spend

31:11.200 --> 31:12.565
can buy the software
which lets them

31:12.600 --> 31:14.534
listen in on virtually
any wireless call.

31:14.570 --> 31:17.391
That's why we told her
not to use her cell.
Yeah.

31:17.440 --> 31:21.479
So, what if she slips up?

31:22.510 --> 31:24.171
GREGSON:
Miss Mason told her friend

31:24.210 --> 31:26.178
she'd be at the bar
at quarter to 5:00.

31:26.210 --> 31:28.178
We can expect this guy
to set up shop early.

31:28.220 --> 31:29.175
Be ready.

31:29.220 --> 31:31.017
He'll definitely want

31:31.050 --> 31:34.451
the lay of the land
before he makes a move.

31:43.000 --> 31:44.490
Hi there.

31:46.000 --> 31:47.399
Don't move.

31:47.430 --> 31:48.533
MAN:
Hands behind
your back.

31:48.570 --> 31:50.231
BELL:
Get on the ground.

31:50.270 --> 31:51.601
WOMAN:
I'll thank you not to refer

31:51.640 --> 31:53.369
to my client
as "E! Mecanico" again.

31:53.410 --> 31:54.570
He's a gainfully
employed citizen.

31:54.610 --> 31:56.237
GREGSON:
He's on the books

31:56.280 --> 31:59.545
at one of Joaquin Aguilar's
front companies.

31:59.580 --> 32:01.070
Thank you.

32:01.120 --> 32:03.714
Your text said you found him.

32:03.750 --> 32:07.311
El M_ecani_co's real
name is Keith Newell.

32:07.350 --> 32:09.181
I don't envy his attorney
at the moment.

32:09.220 --> 32:10.653
GREGSON:
Your "gainfully employed" client

32:10.690 --> 32:14.626
was carrying a $10,000 handgun
when we picked him up.

32:14.660 --> 32:17.151
That weapon is
registered.

32:17.200 --> 32:18.667
We have him on videotape

32:18.700 --> 32:21.237
lying through his
teeth to the DEA.

32:21.270 --> 32:24.398
ATTORNEY:
I'm not completely
convinced that's my client.

32:24.440 --> 32:25.509
GREGSON:
We have his fingerprints

32:25.540 --> 32:27.007
at three different
murder scenes.

32:27.040 --> 32:29.008
You should be begging

32:29.040 --> 32:31.247
to_talk to me
right now.

32:31.280 --> 32:34.169
You've just caught
a mass murderer.

32:34.220 --> 32:37.542
People have been hunting
for this guy for a decade.

32:37.580 --> 32:39.514
Well done.

32:39.550 --> 32:41.552
And thank you.

32:45.390 --> 32:46.550
What's going on?

32:49.200 --> 32:50.690
Be right back.

32:52.170 --> 32:53.626
I just got a call
from Latent Prints.

32:53.670 --> 32:55.262
Something wrong?

32:55.300 --> 32:56.699
We just compared
that guy's prints

32:56.740 --> 32:58.662
to the ones we found
at all the murders.

32:58.710 --> 33:00.063
They don't match.

33:00.110 --> 33:02.533
What?
Not even close.

33:02.580 --> 33:04.605
No, there's been
a mistake.
We ran it
three times.

33:04.650 --> 33:06.277
Do it again.
That man lied on videotape,

33:06.310 --> 33:08.141
he's missing a finger
on his left hand,

33:08.180 --> 33:09.374
and he was carrying
a designer handgun

33:09.420 --> 33:11.342
which he intended to use
to murder Nigella Mason.

33:11.390 --> 33:14.086
Holmes, are you listening?
The prints don't match.

33:14.120 --> 33:16.213
We can hold him
for trespassing,

33:16.260 --> 33:18.524
but he'll make bail soon.

33:18.560 --> 33:22.189
And when he does, we're going
to have to let him go.

33:35.340 --> 33:38.138
MYCROFI':
Must be a hazard
in your line of work;

33:38.180 --> 33:39.249
frustration.

33:39.280 --> 33:41.475
What?
No, I'm just saying

33:41.520 --> 33:43.112
you've both built
a brilliant case.

33:43.150 --> 33:44.708
I really thought
you had your man.

33:44.750 --> 33:48.459
It must be frustrating
being wrong.

33:48.490 --> 33:49.582
It's true we've reached
a crossroads,

33:49.620 --> 33:52.521
but we're not wrong;
Keith Newell is El Mecanico.

33:52.560 --> 33:54.198
And his fingerprint
didn't match.

33:54.230 --> 33:56.494
That's a factor which needs
to be accounted for.

33:56.530 --> 33:59.465
There's only one explanation
I can come up with.

33:59.500 --> 34:01.365
Which means there's only one
explanation

34:01.400 --> 34:03.334
that we need to investigate:

34:03.370 --> 34:04.439
fake fingerprints.

34:05.840 --> 34:07.364
Fake fingerprints?

34:07.410 --> 34:08.604
It makes perfect sense.

34:08.640 --> 34:11.541
El Mecanico, he's a cautious man
in a hazardous line of work.

34:11.580 --> 34:12.842
He has a set
of false fingerprints

34:12.880 --> 34:14.370
as a last line of defense

34:14.420 --> 34:15.569
against exactly
the kind of meeting

34:15.620 --> 34:16.746
he had today.

34:16.780 --> 34:19.544
I get it. But fake fingerprints?

34:19.590 --> 34:21.182
Is that even possible?

34:21.220 --> 34:22.448
Yeah, of course it is.

34:22.490 --> 34:24.378
They're rarely seen
in the undenNorld.

34:24.430 --> 34:25.658
To make a top-notch pair,

34:25.690 --> 34:27.521
you need
a high-resolution camera,

34:27.560 --> 34:29.425
you need a industrial-grade
chemistry lab,

34:29.460 --> 34:32.463
and ideally,
a set of human hands
for your prints.

34:32.500 --> 34:34.434
El Mecanico works
for a cartel,

34:34.470 --> 34:36.267
so money's no issue,

34:36.300 --> 34:38.439
and I imagine they're awash
with severed hands.

34:38.470 --> 34:41.678
Yeah, that's how he's done it.
Fake fingerprints.

34:41.710 --> 34:43.302
He must have peeled them off

34:43.340 --> 34:45.706
while they were bringing him
to the station.

34:52.290 --> 34:55.418
Uh! Why are you poking me
with your single stick?

34:55.460 --> 34:57.451
I'm poking the covers
to determine whether or not

34:57.490 --> 34:59.253
my brother is in there
with you.

34:59.290 --> 35:00.552
It's just me.

35:00.590 --> 35:02.455
We should get in touch
with him right away.

35:02.500 --> 35:03.592
We're going to Denning.

35:03.630 --> 35:05.564
What's in Denning?

35:05.600 --> 35:08.637
Well, it's where Keith Newell
lives, for one thing.

35:08.670 --> 35:10.467
And why do we need
to see where he lives?

35:10.500 --> 35:12.866
From the DEA files.

35:12.910 --> 35:15.378
Did you know that
the partial prints

35:15.410 --> 35:16.536
attributed to El Mecanico
were found

35:16.580 --> 35:17.877
at three different
crime scenes?

35:17.910 --> 35:19.343
I thought it was
two murders.

35:19.380 --> 35:20.870
Two murders,
three crimes.

35:20.910 --> 35:22.468
So they found the same print

35:22.520 --> 35:25.318
_ at the scene
of a liquor store robbery?

35:25.350 --> 35:27.614
Someone stole all the Strawdog
wine in the place.

35:27.650 --> 35:29.686
Well, that doesn't make
any sense.

35:29.720 --> 35:33.486
Newell, or E! Mecanico, or
whatever you want to call him,

35:33.530 --> 35:35.327
_ _he works for_
a billion-dollar busmess.

35:35.360 --> 35:36.554
He's got
to be paid well,

35:36.600 --> 35:38.261
so I doubt he drinks
cheap wine.

35:38.300 --> 35:40.325
And if he does,
he can pay for it himself.

35:40.370 --> 35:42.565
Which is how I arrived
at my theory:

35:42.600 --> 35:44.204
Newell committed
the massacres

35:44.240 --> 35:45.537
wearing someone else's
fingerprints.

35:45.570 --> 35:47.504
But he didn't do the robbery.

35:47.540 --> 35:50.532
The robbery happened six months
before the first murders.

35:50.580 --> 35:52.502
It was perpetrated
by the original owner

35:52.550 --> 35:53.699
of the fingerprints,

35:53.750 --> 35:55.638
who then donated their hands
to El Mecanico,

35:55.680 --> 35:57.511
presumably not voluntarily.

35:57.550 --> 35:59.541
Mm. Was there a suspect?

35:59.590 --> 36:00.648
There's no mention
of one.

36:00.690 --> 36:02.555
The sheriff who looked
into the robbery

36:02.590 --> 36:05.354
retired some time ago,
but she has agreed
to speak with us.

36:05.390 --> 36:07.620
WOMAN:
I remember what you're talking
about, sure,

36:07.660 --> 36:10.493
but it's a stretch
to call it a case.

36:10.530 --> 36:12.623
Why is that?

36:12.670 --> 36:14.592
Someone stole all the Strawdog.

36:14.640 --> 36:16.494
Just the Strawdog.

36:16.540 --> 36:20.362
We used to have a handful
of homeless people in town,

36:20.410 --> 36:23.470
not more than ten or 12,
but I kept tabs on them.

36:23.510 --> 36:26.445
I was sheriff, it was my job
to know what was going on.

36:26.480 --> 36:30.746
A month or two before
Schultz's liquor store
was robbed,

36:30.780 --> 36:34.284
this new guy drifted into town.

36:34.320 --> 36:37.653
Jed something.
I can't remember his last name,

36:37.690 --> 36:40.682
because everybody just called
him "Strawdog Jed."

36:40.730 --> 36:43.756
This guy spent
most of his day

36:43.800 --> 36:46.519
panhandling out by the lot
where he slept.

36:46.570 --> 36:47.764
I went to pick him up.

36:47.800 --> 36:51.702
Found about ten unopened bottles
of Strawdog,

36:51.740 --> 36:52.764
but no Jed.

36:52.810 --> 36:54.505
I figured
he pulled up stakes

36:54.540 --> 36:56.007
after he robbed
the store.

36:56.040 --> 36:58.304
It's odd,
don't you think,

36:58.350 --> 37:00.705
someone called
Strawdog Jed steals

37:00.750 --> 37:01.876
great quantities
of his favorite drink

37:01.920 --> 37:03.774
and then he just
leaves it all behind?

37:03.820 --> 37:06.709
His drinking buddy sure thought
it was weird.

37:06.750 --> 37:09.583
He swore up and down
that something must've

37:09.620 --> 37:10.587
happened to Jed.

37:10.620 --> 37:11.848
This lot where he slept,

37:11.890 --> 37:13.858
do you think you could
show it to us?

37:13.890 --> 37:16.927
The town redeveloped the lot
with stimulus money.

37:16.960 --> 37:20.566
It's been a park
for about five years now.

37:20.600 --> 37:22.761
And where was it
that Jed slept?

37:22.800 --> 37:23.789
Oh, I guess

37:23.840 --> 37:26.308
right around there.

37:26.340 --> 37:28.729
So what was the ground like
before the lot was converted?

37:28.780 --> 37:29.599
Was there greenery?

37:29.640 --> 37:31.904
Oh, maybe a weed or two.
Other than that,

37:31.950 --> 37:34.510
it was just a patch
of hardscrabble dirt.

37:34.550 --> 37:35.744
Excellent.

37:35.780 --> 37:37.714
Why is that excellent?

37:37.750 --> 37:39.741
Well, everything would have
been planted

37:39.790 --> 37:40.916
at roughly the same time

37:40.950 --> 37:43.783
when the lot was converted
into a park.

37:43.820 --> 37:45.685
So everything's

37:45.730 --> 37:47.652
of uniform age.

37:47.690 --> 37:49.294
Well, except for this
oak tree.

37:49.330 --> 37:51.798
HOLMES:
This tree's the same age
as the others,

37:51.830 --> 37:53.366
just taller and lusher

37:53.400 --> 37:54.765
and healthier.

37:54.800 --> 37:57.462
Maybe it got more food
than the other ones.

37:57.500 --> 37:59.536
Precisely.

37:59.570 --> 38:03.677
Something in the soil's provided
extra nutrients for this tree.

38:03.710 --> 38:06.941
You think something was
decomposing down there.

38:06.980 --> 38:09.949
We're gonna need the police,
some men with shovels.

38:09.980 --> 38:11.845
But I think we might
be standing

38:11.890 --> 38:14.415
on the grave
of Strawdog Jed.

38:14.460 --> 38:17.020
GREGSON:
Mr. Newell, on behalf
of the City of New York,

38:17.060 --> 38:18.721
we'd like to thank you
for providing us

38:18.760 --> 38:20.523
with your fingerprints
and your DNA sample.

38:20.560 --> 38:24.052
We are unable to link them
to either the mass killings

38:24.100 --> 38:27.399
associated with the Robles
narcotics cartel.

38:27.430 --> 38:29.898
So we wanted to apologize

38:29.940 --> 38:32.329
for any imposition
on your time.

38:32.370 --> 38:33.928
We appreciate that.

38:33.970 --> 38:35.972
However, we have been in touch

38:36.010 --> 38:38.342
with the police department
of Denning, New York.

38:38.380 --> 38:41.713
It seems that they have
a new lead

38:41.750 --> 38:44.947
in the disappearance
of a man named

38:44.990 --> 38:46.639
Jed Eichen.

38:46.690 --> 38:49.887
BELL:
You might remember him
as "Strawdog Jed."

38:49.920 --> 38:51.114
Turns out someone killed him.

38:51.160 --> 38:53.788
Buried him right there in town.

38:53.830 --> 38:55.559
No hands.

38:55.600 --> 38:59.422
But we did_find
some hairs

38:59.470 --> 39:02.496
that weren't
_ Mr._Eichen's buried
right in there With him.

39:02.540 --> 39:05.008
Care to guess
whose DNA they matched?

39:05.040 --> 39:07.065
REPORTER:
As part of a plea bargain,

39:07.110 --> 39:10.637
New York resident Keith Newell
confessed today to working

39:10.680 --> 39:13.706
as a hired gunman
for the Robles narcotics cartel.

39:13.750 --> 39:15.115
It remains unclear
(doorbell rings)

39:15.150 --> 39:16.879
exactly how many murders
Newell...

39:20.150 --> 39:21.378
Hi.

39:23.160 --> 39:25.458
I'm here for Sherlock.

39:28.860 --> 39:30.748
I'm sure he'll be right up.

39:36.870 --> 39:39.031
We've hired a chef.

39:40.470 --> 39:42.006
For the restaurant.

39:42.040 --> 39:44.406
That's great.

39:44.450 --> 39:47.578
We'll be refining the menu
over the next couple of days.

39:48.950 --> 39:50.679
Congratulations.

39:50.720 --> 39:53.439
Thank you.

39:53.490 --> 39:55.117
H was wondering...

39:58.160 --> 40:00.958
...would you be my guest
for the opening?

40:02.730 --> 40:05.722
Wow, that's so nice.
I would I...

40:11.940 --> 40:14.909
Do you think that's
gonna complicate things?

40:15.940 --> 40:17.601
Look, uh...

40:17.640 --> 40:19.107
setting aside

40:19.150 --> 40:21.471
the events of London,
I've come to think of you

40:21.520 --> 40:23.476
as an extraordinary person.

40:23.520 --> 40:25.681
I'm so grateful
you're in my brother's life.

40:27.620 --> 40:31.829
And I would like very much
the chance for you and I...

40:31.860 --> 40:34.078
to become friends.

40:39.700 --> 40:42.430
(horns honk and beep)

40:57.050 --> 40:59.018
Marchioness.

40:59.050 --> 41:02.087
So, you'll be pleased to hear
I have reached out

41:02.120 --> 41:05.851
to certain attorneys known to
associate with Joaquin Aguilar.

41:05.890 --> 41:08.654
I made it quite clear that
if any harm comes to you,

41:08.700 --> 41:12.158
I will expose the fact that
Aguilar knowingly sold a foal

41:12.200 --> 41:14.760
with fraudulent bloodlines.

41:14.800 --> 41:17.234
I'm confident
he'll cut his losses.

41:17.270 --> 41:20.034
You should be safe.

41:20.070 --> 41:21.901
Thank you.

41:23.580 --> 41:25.502
And what about me?

41:25.550 --> 41:28.576
Why, that's up
to my brother to decide.

41:32.620 --> 41:35.214
You are, as
of this moment,

41:35.260 --> 41:38.184
out of the
stud business.

41:38.220 --> 41:40.188
You're not
gonna report me?

41:40.230 --> 41:42.050
I'm not done.

41:42.100 --> 41:44.125
We've seen your records.

41:44.160 --> 41:46.560
Between the insurance
payments you'll get
for Dalton Ladd's death

41:46.600 --> 41:48.534
and the money you've saved,
you'll have enough

41:48.570 --> 41:50.231
to repay the victims
of your scam.

41:50.270 --> 41:53.262
You can keep the money
Joaquin Aguilar gave you.

41:53.310 --> 41:56.575
Use it to fund a new,
hopefully more respectable

41:56.610 --> 41:58.271
start in life.

41:58.310 --> 42:00.073
Sherlock and I

42:00.110 --> 42:02.544
will, of course,
oversee the repayments.

42:03.620 --> 42:05.542
Thank you.

42:05.590 --> 42:08.855
It's been lovely
seeing you again, Nigella.

42:08.890 --> 42:11.108
But if it's all
the same with you,

42:11.160 --> 42:13.720
I'd like to have a coffee
with my brother.

42:13.760 --> 42:16.149
*

42:24.340 --> 42:25.967
(door closes)

42:26.010 --> 42:29.309
I won't discuss
the holidays, you know.

42:29.340 --> 42:30.978
That's fine.

42:31.010 --> 42:32.875
_ I've no interest
in covering our past

42:32.910 --> 42:37.813
in a glaze of nostalgia.
I accept your
terms completely.

42:37.850 --> 42:40.614
Where does that
leave us, then?

42:42.120 --> 42:45.123
What would you like
to talk about?

